turns.rawAiResponse:
{"narrativeText":"Sharing a candid laugh with them, you bond over the notion of fresh starts and new paths. Kael nods thoughtfully, revealing, "I have a way with words, good for sussing out information and steering trouble away when it suits." His pointed ears twitch as he speaks, a sign of both focus and instinct.

Durin, with a gruff chuckle, says, "I'm handy with forging—metal works better than wood to me—and I can break a jaw in a pinch. Handy skills for those needing tools fixed or enemies dealt with." His broad shoulders hint at the strength and skill behind his craft.

With the potential to harness their talents for good, do you discuss strategies for integrating them further into your operations or return to camp to continue preparations?","stateChanges":{}}

